==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waxwing
<hw>Wax"wing`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of small birds of the genus
<gen>Ampelis</gen>, in which some of the secondary quills are usually
tipped with small horny ornaments resembling red sealing wax. The
Bohemian waxwing (see under <er>Bohemian</er>) and the cedar bird are
examples. Called also <altname>waxbird</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waxwork</ent>⟦br⟧
